# CODEOWNERS — setup-upwarden
#
# This is a customer-facing, credential-handling GitHub Action. Every change to
# it is a change to a supply-chain trust surface, so ALL changes require review
# from the devops/security owners before merge.
#
# Enforcement: this file only gates merges when the default branch has branch
# protection with "Require review from Code Owners" enabled. That toggle is a
# repository setting and must be turned on separately (see SECURITY.md).
#
# Owner handle: @DashUmEr is the team that owns and security-reviews
# this action. Keep the team's membership restricted to devops/security.

# Default owner for everything in the repo.
*                       @DashUmEr

# The trust surface — the action's embedded shell IS the artifact. Called out
# explicitly so these paths can never be merged without a devops/security review,
# even if the default rule above is ever narrowed.
/action.yml             @DashUmEr
/README.md              @DashUmEr

# Governance & security-policy files: changes here alter how vulnerabilities are
# reported, who must review, and the license/provenance guarantees.
/SECURITY.md            @DashUmEr
/CODEOWNERS             @DashUmEr
/LICENSE                @DashUmEr

# CI, release, and provenance/publishing workflows — a compromise here can
# forge or bypass the immutable-release + attestation guarantees.
/.github/               @DashUmEr
